1-convention-organizers/conventionOrganizer.spec.ts
Delete Poll
1-1F-1. Given connected as CO, can delete a pending poll
1-1F-2. Given connected as CO, can delete a ongoing poll
1-1F-3. Given connected as CO, can delete a closed poll
Open Close Poll
1-1C. Given connected as CO can open  poll
1-1D. Given connected as CO can close an open poll
1-1E. Given connected as CO cannot re-open closed poll
Create Poll
1-1A. Given connected as CO can see create poll button
1-1B. Given connected as CO can create a new poll
1-1G. Given connected as CO can create only one poll
1-1I Poll results are shown horizantally
1-1J Given connected as a CO on Create Poll page there are 3 input fields to enter information
User Control
1-2A-1. Given connected as CO can update all fields of user
1-2A-2. CO cannot update representative email with existing email
1-2A-3. CO cannot update representative stake with existing stake
1-2B-1. Should have corresponding workspace delegate and alternate in a same row
1-2B-2. Should have workspace_name ordered alphabetically
1-2C-1. Should not be able to switch active voting power between delegate and alternate when polling is open
1-2C-2. Should not be able to edit user profile when polling is open
1-2D. COs can see who has voted in a poll and how they have voted
Voting Power
1-3A-1. Should be able to switch active voting power between delegate and alternate.
1-3A-2. Only active voter should be able to vote.
2-3-constitutional-delegates-alternate/constitutionalDelegateAlternate.spec.ts
Vote > User: delegate > Voting poll
2-1A. Given active delegate, and poll is open, then vote option should be visible
2-1C. Given active delegate, and poll is open, can update casted vote
2-1F. Given active delegate, can see what they have voted
2-1D. Given active delegate, can choose not to vote
2-1E: Active delegate should be able to vote Yes, No, or Abstain on a poll
Vote > User: delegate > Pending Poll
2-1B. Given active delegate and the poll is pending, voting should be disallowed
Vote > User: alternate > Voting poll
3-1A. Given active alternate, and poll is open, then vote option should be visible
3-1C. Given active alternate, and poll is open, can update casted vote
3-1F. Given active alternate, can see what they have voted
3-1D. Given active alternate, can choose not to vote
3-1E: Active alternate should be able to vote Yes, No, or Abstain on a poll
Vote > User: alternate > Pending Poll
3-1B. Given active alternate and the poll is pending, voting should be disallowed
Representative Status > Representative Status
2-1G. Once login delegate should be able to know their voting right status
3-1G. Once login alternate should be able to know their voting right status
5-access-control-testing/accessControl.spec.ts
Access Control Test > Poll
5-1A. Only CO can create a new poll
5-1B. Only CO can Open Poll
Access Control Test > User Management
5-2A. Only CO can update User Profile
5-2B. Only CO can update Active Voter
6-on-chain-tests.spec.ts
Onchain Poll
6-1A . Given CO, can submit poll results onchain
6-1B. Given votes are uploaded on-chain, all votes are present.
6-1C. Given votes are uploaded on-chain, vote data is correct
